RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 1 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 79. Claiming Purse 29000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STRIKE THE POSE tracked the pace two wide down the backstretch, was in tight between rivals entering the turn, shuffled back a touch three furlongs from home, rallied on the rail at the quarter pole, shifted just outside off the fence in upper stretch and wore down the frontrunner just before the finish. GIVE ME THE BOOTS took command from the start, led the field uncontested down the backside, dictated the pace comfortably throughout the turn, was getting leg weary on the rail in upper stretch, fought to the finish but was collared by the winner nearing the wire and gamely held for second money. TIPSY MOON was unhurried early trailing down the backstretch, began to lengthen stride going four wide around runners midway on the turn, loomed the the threat five wide straightening out for the drive, could not close in at the furlong marker, stalled in deep stretch settling for show at the line, was pulled up galloping out and was vanned off. MO TOWN MADISON stalked in the two path near the rear in the early going, put in a run two wide between runners three eighths from home, showed some interest on the rail down the lane and finished up mildly to the wire for a minor role in the end. INFINITE PASSION stalked three deep at the half, offered a mild run three wide outside horses three furlongs from the finish, shifted out in the four path to be in the mix for a small share turning for home and evened out for a minor role in the final furlong. FOREST MAIDEN settled alone in mid-pack on the rail at the half, was checked mildly behind the troubled runner at the seven sixteenths marker, could see the field through the turn and could not get involved in the stretch drive. MURDER HORNET tracked the pacesetter three wide down the backside, chased the leader in midturn, could not keep up with others when roused at the quarter pole and retreated between runners in mid-stretch. WAR'S END KISS had a good position nestled on the rail, keeping a close eye on the frontrunner down the back straight, was steadied sharply on the fence inside the seven sixteenths marker, lost positions through the turn and could not regroup to be a factor in the stretch run. STEWARDS INQUIRY INTO THE TURN RESULTED IN #7 STRIKE THE POSE BEING DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED LAST FOR INTERFERENCE

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLUEBERRY FIELDS tracked three wide outside runners in the early going, was content to sit outside lurking behind the pacesetter, closed in three wide at the quarter pole, dueled for the lead in the five path at the top of the lane and determinedly got the better of the contesting rival in deep stretch to edge clear for the win at the wire. KEEP GRINDING had a good position on the rail watching the top two early on, was nestled rating comfortably inside down the backstretch, waited throughout the far turn on the fence to pounce, burst between runners in the two path straightening out for the drive, battled with the winner until deep stretch and was just outfinished late in a solid effort, besting the rest. ENCHANT ME settled near the rear inside on the first turn, made little progress on the rail down the backside, was nudged for more three furlongs to go but could not gain on fellow rivals on the final turn and passed the tiring frontrunner in mid- stretch. MAD MOCHA took this field on the rail into the first turn under a modest pace, dictated terms unchallenged through the backstretch, had a narrow diminishing lead at the quarter pole, was collared at the top of the lane outside and faltered on the fence at the furlong marker.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAND AMBITION broke inwardly, tracked in behind the leaders saving ground on the turn, ridden along past the five-sixteenths while dropping back considerably off the leader, came out gradually nearing the furlong grounds under stout urging, surged from between foes to take the lead seventy yards out and cleared. NITEINSHININGARMOR failed to threaten racing toward the back three wide through the turn. SEATTLE POINT settled off the pace and racing off the inside, failed to menace. RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUV TO WIN broke sharp leading early, was then content to sit outside the frontrunner at the half, hounded the pacesetter throughout the running around the bend, surged to take command between rivals in upper stretch and fought on gamely to hold for the narrow victory. NAPA SPIRIT (IRE) was off a step slow to begin, hustled to take command on the rail at the half, hounded outside maintaining a slim advantage on the turn, was collared outside at the top of the stretch, battled stubbornly inside never giving in to the wire but could not re-rally late. GHOUL (BRZ) had a good position on the outside keeping a close eye on the engaging leaders down the backstretch, continued to bide his time outside rivals waiting to move midpoint on the turn, closed in at the quarter pole to loom a serious threat in the five path straightening out for home, needed more late, was gaining mildly at the wire but could not get there in time. WESTERN TROUBLE was off poorly to begin, trailed in the early going, stalked inside in the third flight entering the turn, shifted outside commencing a run with five sixteenths to go, in the six path turning for home was in range of the leaders, showed some energy gaining some late but had to settle for a small piece of the prize in the end. GRAND ALLIANCE stalked near the rear outside of runners down the backstretch, roused to go on midpoint on the turn making a mild rally, was floated out to the seven path being the widest runner at the top of the lane and could not get involved, only passing a weary runner in deep stretch. TRICKY MAGICIAN was tucked in on the rail behind the contesting duo down the back straight, waited to move sitting on the fence through the turn, was asked for run at the quarter pole, offered little response and gave way on the fence in the final sixteenth.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIESTA BEACH tracked between rivals in the three path down the backside, was reined back to let the outside runner press for the lead at the three furlong marker, urged to for more midpoint on the turn, quickly picked up the bit, pounced three wide at the top of the lane and drew away with authority in the final furlong. THAT GIRL ARTEMUS co-trailed outside at the half mile marker, began to pick up runners extended her stride three furlongs from the wire, closed in smartly at the quarter pole, was in the hunt in the seven path turning for home and ran on to the finish to be a clear second best when all was done. VANDOO was in a good spot, all alone, sitting behind the contesting foursome at the half, settled nicely on the fence running through the turn watching the duel up front, was in range on the inside at the top of the lane, angled outside in the four path with run at the furlong marker and closed in to capture third at the wire. CLASSY IMAGE cleared to the lead getting to the rail along the backstretch, was pressured outside throughout the turn, fought on gamely inside in upper stretch, was no match for the winner at the furlong pole giving way and finished up to hold for a minor placing in the end. CANTUCCI stalked outside in midfield with four furlongs remaining, was gaining steadily outside on foes through the turn, had a chance for a piece of the prize six wide for the stretch drive and finished mildly to the wire to be on the fringes. CHASING BOURBON was away slowly at the start, then was rushed up under a ride for better position down the backside on the rail, shifted outside midway on the turn making little impact and could not reach contention through the stretch. VALLEY VICTORY prompted the pace outside down the back straight, could not keep with others dueling for the lead running between horses three eighths to go and weakened with runners on either side in mid-stretch. MEKO MAKEE tracked four wide on the outside in the beginning, was urged to force the issue up front on the outside three furlongs from home, battled on the turn briefly getting the lead, gave way between rivals in upper stretch and stopped in the final sixteenth. NATURAL STAR co-trailed on the inside down the backstretch, was roused for more run at the three eighths marker, lost touch with the field running through the turn and had little to give in the drive to the wire.
